The last date in Poland was March , , and the permit to embark at Bremen was dated in October of that year . 
Here , at least , was a slight chronological framework . 
I assumed , at the start , that the name which had been so carefully cut out of all the documents was the man's own . 
The Elise of the letters was therefore his sister . 
The second letter closed with I have enough work to do , but I keep well . 
Forget thy disappointment so far as I am concerned , for I never expected any thing I don't know why , but I never did . 
Here was a disappointment , at least , to begin with . 
I made a note of it opposite the date , on my blank programme , and took up the next letter . 
It was written in November , , and contained a passage which keenly excited my curiosity . 
It ran thus Do , pray , be more careful of thy money . 
As for thy other request , I have granted it , as thou seest , but it makes me a little anxious . 
What is the joke ? And how can it serve thee ? That is what I do not understand , and I have plagued myself not a little to guess . 
