Mrs. Filch's shawl began to burn my shoulders before I had worn it a half a dozen times . 
Before the next session was half over , I was doubly glad of being safe at home . 
Mrs. Whiston supposed that the increased female representation would give her more support , and indeed it seemed so , at first . 
We read the debates , and my blood fairly boiled when I found what taunts and sneers , and epithets she was forced to endure . 
I wondered how she could sit still under them . 
